# Environment Variables Information
# This file documents all environment variables used by scripts in this project.
# DO NOT put actual values here - this file is committed to version control.
# Create a .env file locally with actual values (see .env.example).

# =============================================================================
# Example Script Variables (say_hello)
# =============================================================================

GREETING_NAME
  Description: Name to include in the greeting message
  Required: No
  Default: "World"
  Example: "John Doe"
  Used by: scripts/say_hello

GREETING_LANGUAGE
  Description: Language code for the greeting
  Required: No
  Default: "en"
  Example: "pt" (Portuguese), "es" (Spanish), "fr" (French), "de" (German)
  Allowed values: en, pt, es, fr, de
  Used by: scripts/say_hello

